  <bioghist id="aspace_a05fc7c83284eb50e84e790128f1183d">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Mitchell Loeb (1889-1968) was an artist and cartoonist whose work reflected his support for labor, liberal Democrats, and Isael.  Loeb was born in Poland and came to the United States as a teenager.  For a short period after World War I, Loeb was an artist for <emph render="italic">The Jewish Daily Forward</emph> and <emph render="italic">The Jewish Day</emph>.  After, he ran a commercial art studio in New York City.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_d87b6cd5a02d7e33a5906ba191af5e0e">
